text.paragraph:
Excessively large dosages of antihistamines, including Promethazine Syrup, in pediatric patients may cause sudden death (see 

                              OVERDOSAGE
                           ). Hallucinations and convulsions have occurred with therapeutic doses and overdoses of Promethazine in pediatric patients. In pediatric patients who are acutely ill associated with dehydration, there is an increased susceptibility to dystonias with the use of promethazine HCl.

Promethazine Syrup should be used with caution in pediatric patients 2 years of age and older (see 

                              WARNINGS-Use in Pediatric Patients
                           ).

Antiemetics should not be used in vomiting of unknown etiology in children and adolescents (see 

                              WARNINGS-Use in Pediatric Patients
                           ).
